review_blob: San Antonio, TX - Total Wine & More - The Rim - 12 oz bottle. Medium golden pour, slight haze, tight white head that leaves some spotty lacing. Aroma has odd peanut-like accents for an IPA. Flavor leaves a lot to be desired, some vegal notes, some of that same peanut-like essence, some raw organic soy bean like essence. Mouthfeel is slightly pasty. Maybe I just got a bad bottle - will try again when in the area again,.

San Antonio, TX - Total Wine & More - The Rim - 12 oz bottle. Dark copper pour, frothy. thick, bone colored head that leaves a nice thick trail of lacing. Aroma has some cherry fruity sweetness, some woody tannic notes. Flavor has some nutty notes, a bit of sweet cherry fruitiness, some light citrus bitterness. Not headed in any real direction. Decently thick mouthfeel.

San Antonio, TX - on tap at Southerleigh. Slight haze to the dark golden pour, thick film of lace on the snow white head. Light vanilla with some spruce hints in the aroma. Bold citrus bitterness in the flavor, some raw cake mix sweetness, a bit of  pineapple fruitiness, some trailing light vanilla in the back end. Solidly, thick rich mouthfeel.
beer_name: Southerleigh Dont Fear the Dank Side

review_blob: San Antonio, TX - on tap at Southerleigh. Deep, dark brown pour, creamy, thick, mocha colored head, nice web of lacing. Aroma has some light chocolate notes, a bit of fresh lake water. Flavor has some hints of curry, a nutty essence, some bakers unsweetened chocolate, faint trailing fruitiness that does equate to coconuts when you try really hard. Smooth creamy mouthfeel. PorterPounder approved.

San Antonio, TX - on tap at Southerleigh, Hazy, dark golden pour, soft, silky white head, nice film of lace. Light smoked meat in the aroma, a hint of chocolate. Flavor presents some light nuttiness, some smoked meat sweetness, . Nice subtle bitterness. Crisp mouthfeel. Solid session starter. lots of flavor for the low ABV.

San Antonio, TX - Total Wine - The Rim - 12 oz can. Pours a hazy, medium orange/golden with a sticky white head that leaves plenty of sticky lacing. Aroma has some decent spruce undertones, a touch of lemon citrus. Somewhat bland flavor, pick up some celery-like vegetable notes, a hint of lemon citrus,faint traces of spearmint spice. Nice spritz to the mouthfeel.

San Antonio, TX - Total Wine - The Rim - 12 oz bottle. Hazy medium orange pout, silky off-white, very thick, frothy head. Aroma has some doughy accents, a touch of peachy fruitiness. Flavor is on the sweet side, some apricot fruitness, a light touch of spearmint, some light trailing citrus bitterness. Mouthfeel has a nice solid textured feel to it.

Fredericksburg, Tx - Ottos German Bistro, on tap. Viscous black pour, no discernible head. Sour, vinegar-like aroma. Taste is the same, but in a goodway, red wine vinegar, raspberry tartness. Velvety smooth mouthfeel.

San Antonio, Tx - BJs - I-10 NW - on tap. Labeled as Edeavor IPA. Medium copper pour, soft, but quickly fading off-white head. Aroma of orange marmalade, a touch of funky feet. Solid, bold full-bodied flavor with some juicy citrus bitterness, some caramel sweetness, a touch of pineapple and mango fruitiness. Solid, thick, rich mouthfeel.

Rating #6900! Tallahassee, Fl - Beer Stop - 12 oz can. Dull, medium golden pour, no head to speak of. Aroma has some muted blueberry sourness, faint vanilla if you try hard. Flavor has some blueberry sourness, a bit of vanilla sweetness, kind of artificial, trialing bubble gum candiness, Mouthfeel has a decent spritz to it. Not sure where this one was heading, missed the mark.
beer_name: Two Henrys Belleview Biltmore Blueberry Vanilla Wheat

review_blob: Tallahassee, Fl - New Leaf Market - Bradfordville - 12 oz can. Sparkling, ligjt golden pour, no head. Crisp aroma of ginger and Golden Delicious apples. Flavor had a nice spicy ginger bite to it, some crisp apple notes in the finish. Peppery mouthfeel. Not bad.

Tallahassee, Fl - Beer Stop - 22 oz bomber. Slight haze to the medium orange pour, sticky, bone colored medium thick bone colored head that leaves a nice film of lacing. Nice, fragrant aroma with some solid spruce accents, some floral hints. Solid, bittersweet citrusy hop flavor, some pineapple fruitiness, a bit of cake mix sweetness to round it out. Rich, thick sticky mouthfeel. Pretty solid.

Tallahassee, Fl - Beer Stop - 12 oz bottle. Light-medium golden pour, slight haze, initial bubbly snow white head, fades quickly. Aroma has some pleasant, interesting Cajun spices. Flavor has a bit of heat to it, some cayenne pepper, a bit of seafood brine, some vegal notes. Interesting to say the least. Thick enough mouthfeel.

Tallahassee, Fl - Beer Stop - 12 oz can. Sparkling medium gold pour, soft, bubbly white head with a nice web of lacing. Aroma has a nice mango essence to it, light spearmint. Pleasant flavor, nice citrus hop bite, fresh mango fruitniness, a bit of spearmint spice in the back end. Mouthfeel has just a hint of tinniness to it.

Tallahassee, Fl - Wal Mart - Mahan Drive - 12 oz classically styled mountain landscape can, reminiscent of early Busch cans. Pour is luxuriously translucent and sparkling with a nice light golden hue. The head is bubbly and white and is determined not to stick around. Tiny spherical bubbles playfully dance throughout my enjoyment of this delightful elixir. After the breathtaking view of this lovely beverage, I desire to experience the aroma. My nose tingles with the essence of wet copper pennies, some spent hard candy. My senses being overloaded, I have just enough capacity to take inventory of the flavor. Saved the best for last Im thinking as the club soda notes tickle my tongue, some light salt water, just a hint of of paper bag. Mouthfeel is decidedly thin as it slides over the tongue, Bought a whole case, will be my lawnmower beer this summer; will go down well after tossing in the freezer.

Tallahassee, Fl - ABC Fine Wine & Spirits - Betton - 22 oz bomber. Dark brown pour, tight off-white head that fades after a while. Aroma of cherries, dates and brown sugar. Flavor is full-bodied and belly warming, some brown sugar sweetness, some dates and raisins, a touch of light chocolate. Mouthfeel has a nice thickness to it. Good for sipping late into the night.
beer_name: Heavy Seas Uncharted Waters: Plank IV

review_blob: Tallahassee, Fl - ABC Fine Wine & Spirits - 12 oz bottle. Medium golden, slight haze, no head. Aroma is pleasantly peachy, surprisingly natural. Flavor has a solid peach fruitiness to it. Hints of Golden Delicious apples, a bit of vanilla sweetness in the back end. Clean mouthfeel.
beer_name: Ciderboys Peach County Apple Peach Hard Cider

review_blob: Tallahassee, Fl. - Publix Supermarket - 22 oz bomber. Pours a sparkling medium orange withe a creamy, sticky white head that leaves a nice coat of lacing. Aroma has some light spruce accents, a bit of maple syrup sweetness. Flavor is sweet with some very light citrus, juicy fruit gum, some honeydew melon, a hint of maple syrup and a touch of hard candy sweetness. Mouthfeel is syrupy in a good way. Comparing my notes to the former Gemini, the earlier one was a bit more subtle and sharper.

Tallahassee, Fl - ABC Fine Wine & Spirits - Betton - 12 oz bottle. Sparkling, medium copper pour, light off white head. Aroma has some pungent maple syrup accents. Full-bodied flavor, caramel, pineapple fruitiness, some trailing citrus bitterness. Thick, sticky mouthfeel.

Tallahassee, Fl - ABC Fine Wine & Spirits - Betton - 12 oz bottle. Sparkling, medium orange pour, faint trace of a bone colored head. Aroma has some candied orange accents, slightly artificial. Flavor is that of orange jello, hard candy, more orange flavor than real citrus bitterness. Mouthfeel is thick enough.

Tallahassee, Fl - ABC Fine Wine & Spirits - Betton - 12 oz can. Hazy, light golden pour, clingy, off-white head. Aroma has some passion fruit accents, a touch of coriander spice. Flavor runs along the same lines as the aroma. Nice tartness with some bubble gum hints in the finish. Nice spritz to the mouthfeel.

Tallahassee, Fl - ABC Fine Wine & Spirits - 12 oz bottle. Sparkling medium copper pour, slight off-white head. Heavy aroma with a solid piney bent to it, some fruity pineapple accents. Flavor is solid, with some solid citrus accents, some sweet caramel, a bit of crystal malt overkill, does not ruin it though. Decently thick mouthfeel.

Tallahassee, Fl - ABC Fine Wine & Spirits - Betton - 12 oz bottle - sparkling medium golden pour, light snow white head that dissipates quicly. Aroma has some light yeasty accents, a touch of floral spiciness. Crisp flavor, some peppery accents, a touch of spearmint, some buttery notes in the back end. Crisp mouthfeel. Decent.

Tallahassee, Fl - on tap at at Liberty Bar and Restaurant. Sparkling dark orange pour, frothy, off white head with a delicate web of lace. Boozy aroma, but not off- putting, some kids cereal sweetness, but not cloying. Flavor has some caramel, a bit of maple syrup, some  brown sugar, solid sweetness, but not cloying at all. Thick, rich mouthfeel.

Tallahassee, Fl - ABC Fine Wine & Spirits - Betton - 12 oz bottle. Slightly sparkling medium golden pour, Aroma of golden delicious applas and strawberry juice Flavor has some light strawberry notes, basic golden delicious apple flavor, a hint of pear fruitiness. Mouthfeel is smooth enough,

Tallahassee, Fl - Momos Pizza, on tap. Sparkling, light copper pour, soft, snow white head, light lacing. Sweet aroma, hints of rye spiciness. Nutty rye mintiness, mellow melon fruitiness, toffee in finish. Thick, rich mouthfeel.
beer_name: Victory 2015 Hop Ticket #2 Dry Hopped Saison

review_blob: Tallahassee, Fl, on tap at Momos. Hazy, light orange pour, slight white head, light lacing. Aroma of light honey, some melon fruitiness. Flavor has some bland honey sweetness light bubble gum, copper pennies. Hint of spice in finish. Smooth mouthfeel.

Tallahassee,Fl. - on tap at Proof Brewing.  Very hazy, light golden colored pour,  thin snow white head. Faint aroma of passion fruit, some guava, a solid dose of sourness. Nice sour guava and passion fruit in the flavor. Slightly biotic, but not off-putting. Nice spritz to the mouthfeel. .
beer_name: Proof Evil Kiss - Guava Passion Fruit

review_blob: Tallahassee, Fl - on tap at Proof Brewing. Dark brown pour, mocha colored head. Aroma has the essence of a breakfast in a sidewalk cafe with hints of coffee, orange juice and cinnamon rolls. Orange-chocolate candy accents, some fresh brewed coffee, a touch of cinnamon.  Smooth mouthfeel. Nice addition to the lineup.
beer_name: Proof Ghost Totem - Orange Cinnamon Coffee

review_blob: Tallahassee, Fl. - Proof Brewing, on tap. Dark black pour, mocha colored head, thick lacing. Aroma has some chocolate accents, a touch of pepper spiciness, some rubbery accents in the aroma. Good pepper burn to go along with the  cocoa accents, a touch of licorice sweetness. Hint of cinnamon in finish. Mouthfeel has a decent slickness to it,

Tallahassee, Fl. - on tap at Proof Brewing. Hazy light orange appearance, snow white head, decent lacing. Aroma has some lemony accents, a touch of sour candy. Flavor has excellent puckerness, some lemon, citrus accents, a touch of Lemonheads candy, Excellent pucker, with a solid spritz in the mouthfeel. Solid.

Tallahassee, Fl - ABC Fine Wine & Spirits - Betton - 12 oz bottle. Sparkling, dark copper pour, long lasting snow white head. Aroma has some sweet doughy accents, a touch of spruce. Full-bodied flavor, some sweet citrus accents, some mango fruitiness, some caramel sweetness, more malt oriented than bitter. Thickish, rich mouthfeel.

Tallahassee, Fl - ABC Fine Wine &u; Spirits - Bull Run. Dark brown pour with an off-white head that leaves a fair amount of lacing. Aroma has some chocolate notes, a touch of creosote, hints of chipotle peppers . Flavor is full bodied with some chocolate nib notes, a hint of chipotle peppers, a wisp of vanilla, and some back end earthy topsoil and creosote. Mouthfeel has a nice chalky thickness with a solid pepper burn.
beer_name: Highland The Kinsman Project: Black Mocha Stout w/ Cacao Nibs & Chipotle

beer_brewer_name: Leinenkugel Brewing Company (Tenth & Blake Beer Co.)
review_blob: Tallahassee, Fl - ABC Fine Wine & Spirits - 12 oz bottle. Light golden pour, very brief , light off-white head. Very light sour aroma with some ripening fruit notes. Flavor has some solid sour notes, a touch of bubble gum, some sweet tart candy sour notes, but overall misses the mark. Decent spritz to the mouthfeel.

Tallahassee, Fl - New Leaf Market - 12 o can. sparkling medium copper pour, not much of a head. Aroma has some heavy coffee accents, some pepper-like earthiness. Interesting earthy flavor with strong coffee accents, some pepper-like vegal notes, a touch of date-like sweetness in the background. Pleasantly thick mouthfeel. Very enjoyable.
beer_name: Maui Brewing Doppel Shot Double Bock

review_blob: Tallahassee, Fl - New Leaf Market - 12 oz can. Sparkling, medium copper pour, light, but persistent bubbly white head. Aroma is kind of funky, some essence of smelly feet, a touch of wort. Flavor has some brown sugar sweetness, a light hint of citrus bitterness, some caramel to round it out. Mouthfeel has a kind of pasty essence to it. Overall, not bad, just not all that refreshing and does not go down that easy.

Tallahassee, Fl - ABC Fine Wine & Spirits - Betton - 12 oz bottle. Cloudy, medium golden pour, looks like grapefruit juice. Aroma of a mimosa, more citrus like than apple, Flavor has some light orange citrus notes, basic golden delicious apple flavor, a hint of pear fruitiness. Mouthfeel is smooth enough,

Tallahassee, Fl - on tap at BJs. Hazy, dark orange with a filmy snow white head that leaves a trace of lacing. Aroma has some peach juice accents, a hint of coriander spice. Pleasant peach fruitiness, a hint of citrus bitterness, a touch of bubble him sweetness. Nice spritz to the mouthfeel.

Tallahassee, Fl. - Trader Joes -12 oz bottle. Dark orange pour has a slight haze to it with a silky snow white head that sticks around a while. Light spruce to the aroma, a touch of nuttiness. Solid flavor, light citrus bitterness, some, light pineapple fruitiness, a touch of spearmint. Mouthfeel has a decent thickness to it. Enjoyable.

Tallahassee, Fl - Proof Brewing Company - on tap. Hazy, medium orange pour, soft, snow white head, decent lacing clings to the edge of the glass. Canned pineapple juice and coriander in the aroma. Flavor has some pineapple juice accents, a hint of bubble gum in the back end with an overriding essence of coriander permeating throughout, mango evident in the finish. Refreshing on a early spring day enjoying the patio at Proof.

Tallahassee, Fl - Proof Brewing Company - on tap. Hazy, light orange pour, soft, snow white head, decent lacing. Aroma has a decent citrus bent to it, some light spruce accents Flavor has decent solid citrus back bone, some Tang orange drink accents, a bit of cake mix sweetness. Mouthfeel is pleasantly thick.
beer_name: Proof EightFive-0 Pale Ale - Citrus Zest

review_blob: Tallahassee, Fl. - Market Square Liquors - 750 ml cage corked bottle. Slight haze to the medium golden pour with a silky soft white head that leaves a nice film of lacing. Aroma is pleasant, not overly apparent with some light saffron spiciness a touch of grassiness. Classic Belgian flavor with clean pear-like fruitiness, touch of yeast, some saffron spiciness. Mouthfeel has a solid spritz to it. Very satisfying.
beer_name: Ommegang Game of Thrones #6 - Seven Kingdoms

review_blob: Tallahassee, Fl - Beer Stop - 22 oz bomber. Sparkling medium golden pour, silky, snow white head with decent lacing. Aroma has a pleasant ginger twang to it with a hint of spearmint. Solid citrus backbone to the frontal friendly assault of ginger. which is not overbearing or distracting but is the dominant flavor. Hints of pineapples as well, which seems to kind of being a house flavor for Ballast, in a good way. Pleasantly thick mouthfeel. Solid as usually the case from Ballast Point.
beer_name: Ballast Point Big Eye IPA - Ginger

review_blob: Tallahassee, Fl - Beer Stop - 16 oz nitro can. Nitro induced viscous oily black pour with a sticky khaki colored head that leaves a nice coat of lacing. Aroma has some earthy accents with some freshly tilled dirt, a touch of coffee. Flavor has a nice roasted profile to it with some light chocolate accents, a bit of potting soil and some day old percolated coffee. Mouthfeel has a decent rich thickness to it. Pretty solid.

Tallahassee, Fl - Beer Stop - Sparkling medium - light golden pour, bubbly white head, light lacing. Light hint of spearmint and spruce in the aroma. Refreshing, crisp flavor with light bitter citrus notes, a touch of spearmint spiciness and a faint whisper of caramel sweetness. Mouthfeel doesnt have that breathless quality to it that some low ABV session IPAs have - this is nice and crisp.

Tallahassee, Fl - Beer Stop - 12 oz bottle. Hazy, dark golden pour, fluffy snow-white head, decent lacing. Aroma is slightly biotic and earthy, hints of lemon and coriander. Flavor has some coriander notes, some citrusy lemon notes, some yeasty notes with a hint of raw cake mix. Mouthfeel has a spritz to it.

Tallahassee,, FL - Beer Stop - 12 oz bottle. Murky medium orange pour, light white head, no lacing. Floral-accented aroma, hint of grassiness. Flavor is pleasant, pick up some summery lemony notes, a touch of apricot-like fruitiness, some faint saffron-like spiciness. Clean, crisp mouthfeel. Very refrshing and good session material.

Tallahassee, Fl - Beer Stop - 12 oz can. Lazy, light-copper pour with an initial bubbly off-white head that fades quickly Aroma has some brief lemon accents, a touch of hard candy sweetness. Dull flavor, light coriander and bubble presence, hint of lemon citrus, do not puck up the advertised basil, odd spicy notes in the finish but not basil-like, Slight metallic twang to the mouthfeel.

Tallahassee, Fl - ABC Fine Wine & Spirits - 16 oz can.Medium golden pour, slight haze, tight off-white head that clings to the edge of the glass. Aroma has a hint of spruce, some white grape juice. flavor is malt oriented, some light molasses. some passion fruit sweetness, just a hint of light citrus bitterness, some yeasty notes in the back end, boozy finish.

Tallahassee, Fl - Publix Supermarkets - Killearn - 12 oz bottle. Medium golden pour with a slight haze, tight off-white head. Light cat urine aroma with a light spicy bent. Standard catty session IPA flavor, light citrus bent, hint of saffron spice, spearmint in the back end. Crisp refreshing mouthfeel. Decent.
